Class Program

public class Program extends Object

  • Constructor Details

    • Program

      public Program(int nQubits, Step... moreSteps)
      Create a Quantum Program and indicate how many qubits will be involved. By default, all qubits are initialized to the |0 > state.
      Parameters:
      nQubits - the amount of qubits that will be used in this program
      moreSteps - steps to add to the program

  • Method Details

    • initializeQubit

      public void initializeQubit(int idx, double alpha)
      Initialize this qubit. The qubit will be in a state \psi = \alpha |0 > + \beta |1 > . Since \alpha^2 + \beta^2 should equals 1, only \alpha is required.
      Parameters:
      idx - the index of the qubit to be initialized
      alpha - the alpha value of the qubit state.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - in case the index of the qubit is higher than the amount of qubits -1 .

    • addStep

      public void addStep(Step step)
      Adds a step with one or more gates to the existing program. In case the Step contains an operation that would put a measured qubit into a potential superposition again, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown.
      Parameters:
      step - the step to be added to the program

    • addSteps

      public void addSteps(Step... moreSteps)
      Adds multiple steps with one or more gates to the existing program. In case the Step contains an operation that would put a measured qubit into a potential superposition again, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown.
      Parameters:
      moreSteps - steps to be added to the program
